body:
Hello,

Could Verilator support partial struct initialization ?

```
typedef struct packed {
    logic a;
    logic b;
} test_t;

module example (
    input  logic clk,
    input  logic a,
    input  logic b,
    output logic c
);
 
    test_t test;
           test.a = 1'b0;
 
    always_ff @(posedge clk) begin
        test.a <= a;
        test.b <= b;
 
        c <= test.a || test.b;
    end

endmodule
```

Verilator outputs:

```
verilator --lint-only --Wall example.sv
%Error: example.sv:15:13: syntax error, unexpected '=', expecting IDENTIFIER or randomize
   15 |      test.a = 1'b0;
```
   
```
verilator -cc example.sv
%Error: example.sv:15:13: syntax error, unexpected '=', expecting IDENTIFIER or randomize
   15 |      test.a = 1'b0;
      |             ^
```
The use cases are mostly FPGA related, afaik.
Thank you.
